Field Detail

insideOld

private int insideOld
State variable to keep track of whether we currently are inside a BML \old expression. This is the case if and only if insideOld > 0. The reason why we do not use a simple flag but a counter instead is to support possibly nested \old expressions.

Method Detail

getHeap

private java.lang.String getHeap()
Returns the name of the heap variable to be used in the current context of the translation. The actual heap to be used thereby depends on whether we currently are inside a BML \old expression or not.

Returns:
The name of the heap variable to be used in the current context of the translation.

addBoundVariables

private void addBoundVariables(int count)
Adds count new bound variables to the current context of the translation. The new variables are given names which are unique the current context.

count - The number of new bound variables to add to the current context of the translation.
